<subSubSection id="37852D97FFFBF001AE72CBC4FB17FDA4" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7F207E1CFFFBF001AE72CBC4FB17FDA4" blockId="1.[810,1452,466,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="4DEBA20EFFFBF001AE72CBC4FC3BFD83" bold="true" box="[863,998,503,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after 
<collectingRegion id="BD5BB0FEFFFBF001A9BCCBC4FB29FD83" box="[1169,1268,503,529]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, and the genus name 
<taxonomicName id="B89F059FFFFBF001AE40C82FFC34FDA4" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[877,1001,540,566]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Calopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DEBA20EFFFBF001AE40C82FFC34FDA4" box="[877,1001,540,566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Calopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37852D97FFFBF001AE72C872FABCFCCF" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7F207E1CFFFBF001AE72C872FABCFCCF" blockId="1.[810,1452,466,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="4DEBA20EFFFBF001AE72C872FC04FDC9" bold="true" box="[863,985,577,603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing venation characters only. Postnodal very numerous (
<emphasis id="4DEBA20EFFFBF001AEC2C854FBCCFD12" box="[1007,1041,615,640]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">ca.</emphasis>
60); short sclerotized pterostigma covering few cells; base of IR1 very distad that of RP2 (11 cells); no apparent distal fork of RP2; base of first intercalary between IR1 and RP1 midway between base of RP2 and pterostigma; MP and CuA weakly curved; CuAb short and weak; no secondary longitudinal vein in cubito-anal area; RP3/4 apparently distally forked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
